.TH MI_OFFSET_PARAM 9 "@PACKAGE_DATE@" "@PACKAGE@-@VERSION@" "@PACKAGE_TITLE@ DDI/DKI"
.\"
.\"
.SH NAME
.B mi_offset_param
\- find parameter offset in a \fISTREAMS\fR message block
.\"
.\"
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.B #define _MPS_SOURCE
.br
.B #include <sys/stream.h>
.br
.B #include <sys/ddi.h>
.br
.B #include <sys/mpsddi.h>
.HP
.BI "unsigned char *mi_offset_param(mblk_t *" mp ", long " offset ", long " len );
.HP
.BI "unsigned char *mi_offset_paramc(mblk_t *" mp ", long " offset ", long " len );
.\"
.\"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.PP
.TP
.I mp
a message pointer specifying the message into which to calculate the parameter offset.
.PD 0
.TP
.I offset
the offset of the parameter within the message,
.IR mp .
.TP
.I len
the length of the parameter within the message.
.PD
.\"
.\"
.SH INTERFACE
.PP
.IR MPS \(rg-specific
DDI.
.\"
.\"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.BR mi_offset_param ()
and
.BR mi_offset_paramc ()
are
.IR MPS \(rg-specific
helper functions that can be used to locate parameter extents within messsage
blocks and message block chains.
.BR mi_offset_param ()
and
.BR mi_offset_paramc ()
are single block and chain versions of the same utility.
.PP
.BR mi_offset_param ()
returns a pointer to the parameter extent within the message block pointed to
by
.I mp
that exists at the offset,
.IR offset ,
and is of length,
.IR len .
The entire exent must be contained within the
.I b_rptr
and
.I b_wptr
of the data block within which the parameter extent exists.
.BR
.BR mi_offset_paramc ()
is the chain message block version of
.BR mi_offset_param ()
and will return the memory extent within a chain of message blocks.  The
offset,
.IR offset ,
is from the first byte
.RI ( b_rptr )
of the first
.BR datamsg (9)
data block in the message.
.\"
.\"
.SH USAGE
.PP
.BR mi_offset_param ()
and
.BR mi_offset_paramc ()
can be useful for finding addresses and the like given an offset into the
message block, such as is often needed when working with
.BR tpi (7)
primitives such as
.BR T_BIND_REQ (7).
.\"
.\"
.SH RETURN
.PP
When
.BR mi_offset_param ()
or
.BR mi_offset_paramc ()
succeed, they return a pointer to the memory extent containing the parameter;
when they fail, they return
.BR NULL .
.\"
.\"
.SH ERRORS
.PP
.BR mi_offset_param ()
and
.BR mi_offset_paramc ()
fail when the memory extent described by
.IR offset " and " len
would not fit within the data area of the passed in message,
.IR mp .
.\"
.\"
.SH CONTEXT
.PP
.BR mi_offset_param ()
and
.BR mi_offset_paramc ()
can be called from any context.  However, consideration should be given on the
impact of these functions before they are called from an interrupt service
routine.
.\"
.\"
.SH MP-STREAMS
.PP
.BR mi_offset_param ()
and
.BR mi_offset_paramc ()
are MP-safe.  The caller, however, is responsible for ensuring exclusive
access to the passed in message.
.\"
.\"
.SH NOTICES
.PP
.BR mi_offset_param ()
and
.BR mi_offset_paramc ()
are
.IR MPS \(rg-specific
functions:
.BR _MPS_SOURCE ,
.B _AIX_SOURCE
or
.B _MAC_SOURCE
must be defined before including DDI/DKI include files to expose this symbol.
.BR "@PACKAGE_TITLE@"
must also have been compiled with
.BR CONFIG_STREAMS_COMPAT_MPS ,
.BR CONFIG_STREAMS_COMPAT_MPS_MODULE ,
.BR CONFIG_STREAMS_COMPAT_AIX ,
.BR CONFIG_STREAMS_COMPAT_AIX_MODULE ,
.BR CONFIG_STREAMS_COMPAT_MAC
or
.B CONFIG_STREAMS_COMPAT_MAC_MODULE
defined.
.\"
.\"
.SH IMPLEMENTATION
.PP
.BR mi_offset_param ()
and
.BR mi_offset_paramc ()
are simply implemented by walking through the message blocks until an offset
is reached and providing a pointer to the extent at the offset with the proper
length.
.\"
.\"
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.PP
.BR mpscompat (9),
.BR aixcompat (9),
.BR maccompat (9),
.BR STREAMS (9).
.\"
.\"
.SH BUGS
.PP
.BR mi_offset_param ()
and
.BR mi_offset_paramc ()
have no known bugs.
.\"
.\"
.SH COMPATIBILITY
.PP
.BR mi_offset_param ()
and
.BR mi_offset_paramc ()
are
compatible with
.IR MPS \(rg,
.IR AIX \(rg,
.IR MacOT \(rg,
and
.IR Solaris \(rg,
with the following portability considerations:
